***********************************************************************

Call for Participation

ICSOC 2014  : 12th International Conference on Service Oriented Computing

3-6 November 2014, Paris, France

http://www.icsoc.org/

***********************************************************************

You are kindly invited to participate in the 12th International=20=20
Conference on Service Oriented Computing (ICSOC). ICSOC is the top=20=20
international forum for academics, industry researchers, developers,=20=20
and practitioners to report and share groundbreaking work in=20=20
service-oriented computing. ICSOC fosters cross-community scientific=20=20
excellence by gathering experts from various disciplines, such as=20=20
business process management, distributed systems, computer networks,=20=20
wireless and mobile computing, cloud computing, networking, scientific=20=20
workflows, services science, management science, and software=20=20
engineering. ICSOC 2014 will bring together scientists, engineers, and=20=20
practitioners from multiple disciplines to focus on service-oriented,=20=20
cloud-based, innovative enterprises ready for the 21st century. The=20=20
conference will feature research and industry presentations,=20=20
forward-looking keynote presentations, workshops, demonstrations, and=20=20
a PhD track.

The conference will take place in Paris, France. Paris is known as the=20=20
world's most romantic city.  Whether you travel with a partner or fly=20=20
solo, the charms of this city are irresistible.  You can live the=20=20
romance by staying at one of Paris' many enchanting boutique hotels.=20=20
ICSOC 2014 will be hosted by Paris Dauphine University and Telecom=20=20
SudParis, which is often ranked as one of the best European=20=20
engineering school.

For travel arrangements, please check
http://events.telecom-sudparis.eu/icsoc/Attendees/Attendees1.php

Online registration is available at
http://events.telecom-sudparis.eu/icsoc/Attendees/Attendees2.php

